# FlagFit Pro - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
FlagFit Pro is a flag football training application built with Angular 21 and Supabase.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Angular 21 (standalone components, signals, zoneless change detection)
- **UI Library**: PrimeNG v21 (CSS animations, no @angular/animations needed)
- **Backend/Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Realtime, Edge Functions)
- **Styling**: SCSS with CSS custom properties (design tokens)
- **Build**: Vite
- **Testing**: Vitest, Playwright

## Angular 21 Patterns (CRITICAL)

### Always Use:
1. **Standalone components** - No NgModules
2. **`inject()` function** - Not constructor injection
3. **Signals** for reactive state - `signal()`, `computed()`, `effect()`
4. **Control flow syntax** - `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` (not *ngIf, *ngFor)
5. **OnPush change detection** - `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
6. **Signal inputs/outputs** - `input()`, `output()` when possible

### Example Component Pattern:
```typescript
import { Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy, signal, computed, inject } from "@angular/core";
import { CommonModule } from "@angular/common";

@Component({
  selector: "app-example",
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule],
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  template: `
    @if (isLoading()) {
      <div>Loading...</div>
    }
    @for (item of items(); track item.id) {
      <div>{{ item.name }}</div>
    }
  `,
})
export class ExampleComponent {
  private myService = inject(MyService);
  
  isLoading = signal(false);
  items = signal<Item[]>([]);
  hasItems = computed(() => this.items().length > 0);
}
```

## Service Pattern:
```typescript
@Injectable({ providedIn: "root" })
export class MyService {
  private http = inject(HttpClient);
  private supabase = inject(SupabaseService);
  
  private readonly _data = signal<Data | null>(null);
  readonly data = this._data.asReadonly();
}
```

## File Naming Conventions
- Components: `kebab-case.component.ts`
- Services: `kebab-case.service.ts`
- Guards: `kebab-case.guard.ts`
- Models/Interfaces: `kebab-case.model.ts` or `kebab-case.interface.ts`

## Directory Structure
```
angular/src/app/
├── core/           # Services, guards, interceptors, models
├── shared/         # Reusable components, directives, pipes
├── features/       # Feature modules (dashboard, training, analytics)
└── app.config.ts   # App configuration
```

## Styling Rules
- **Always use design tokens** (CSS custom properties)
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography values
- Use `var(--space-*)`, `var(--color-*)`, `var(--text-*)`, `var(--radius-*)`

## Database (Supabase)
- All database operations go through Supabase client
- Use RLS (Row Level Security) policies
- Migrations in `database/migrations/` or `supabase/migrations/`
- Edge Functions in `supabase/functions/`

## Code Quality
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- Use explicit types (avoid `any`)
- Double quotes for strings
- 2-space indentation
- Semicolons required
- Trailing commas in multi-line structures

## Don't:
- Don't use NgModules
- Don't use constructor injection (use inject())
- Don't use BehaviorSubject when signals work
- Don't use *ngIf/*ngFor (use @if/@for)
- Don't hardcode style values
- Don't use Zone.js (app is zoneless)

